The paper deals with the design and evaluation of coding schemes for networked distributed storage systems, which involves aspects of distributed computing (DC), information theory (IT), and networking (NI). The paper also considers the trade-offs between different performance metrics, which is a common theme in systems (SY) and cryptography (CR) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC, followed by cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.CR.
